                      (Psalm 29, ET) letters alternate black and red on four consecutive lines for the phrase <q>“Ascribe to the Lord.”</q></desc>
                    <desc>Columetric layout of text: various points throughout the psalms, e.g., <locus target="#19r #71v #72r" facs="023 076 076">folss. 19r, 71v, 72r, </locus>; <locus target="#107r" facs="111">107r, </locus> (Ps. 145); <locus target="#109r" facs="113">109r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#114r" facs="118">114r, </locus> (fourth biblical canticle); <locus target="#117v #118r" facs="122">117v, 118r, </locus> (tenth biblical canticle), <locus target="#124v" facs="129">124v</locus> (third section of the Song of Songs)</desc>
